text.tspan: Long-term homicide rates across Western Europe, 1250 to 2020
Long-term homicide rates across a select number of countries or regional groups in Western Europe. This is measured
as the number of homicides per 100,000 individuals in a given population.
Data source: Eisner (2014) & WHO Mortality Database (2022)
